HEADWORD: calabura
<hw>calabura</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a fast-growing tropical American
evergreen (<spn>Muntingia calabura</spn>) having white flowers and white
fleshy edible fruit; bark yields a silky fiber used in cordage and wood
is valuable for staves.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Jamaican cherry, calabur tree, silkwood.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

